HEADWORD: Pratincole
<hw>Pra"tin*cole</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any bird of the Old World genus <gen>Glareola</gen>, or family
<fam>Glareolid⟦ae⟧</fam>, allied to the plovers. They have long, pointed
wings and a forked tail.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pratingly</ent>⟦br⟧
